  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: At 05:17 ET, Like Whitten with Dayton Freight Line notified ERTS of a cargo release at 800 Commerce Parkway South Drive, Greenwood, IN. It was reported that approximately 2 ounces of Bonderite C-AK 319 Alkaline Cleaner was released from a 275-gallon IBC Tote due to the seal being damaged. The tote was placed in the warm room and the product was cleaned with acid powder, placed in a plastic bucket, and put on top of the tote. The release impacted the top of the tote around the cap.

  • Description: At 02:34 ET, Joseph Rucinski with Dayton Freight Lines contacted ERTS to report a five-gallon spill of regulated UN1263 "Permashield 431" that was released at 800 Commerce Pkwy S Dr, Greenwood, IN 46143, USA. The caller advised that terminal personnel completed the cleanup placing the spilled material into a 10-gallon metal drum.

item.description:
Report E-2024010253

Identified by scraper @ 2024-01-19T00:34:31+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2023-10-17
  • City: CONNERSVILLE
  • State: IN
  • Report Type: Undeclared Shipment with no Release
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: RECLAIMED ENERGY CO., INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: The material shipped as 32/55-gallon drums (received on 10/17/23) of flammable liquids for recycling. The material was attempted to be recycled but did not result in an usable product. This resulted in the material not qualifying as a Hazardous Secondary Material. The material was managed as a hazardous waste with the waste codes of F005, F003, D001, and D035. Reclaimed Energy is permitted to accept these waste codes and managed the waste in an appropriate manner. The generator has been notified.
